The paper deals with the computational complexity of processing massive data sets, which is a central topic in computer science. The focus is on distributed computing, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions communication complexity and streaming algorithms, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
